Package: wg-gtk-client
Version: @VERSION@
Section: net
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: python3, python3-gi, gir1.2-gtk-3.0, wireguard-tools, policykit-1, curl, nftables, iputils-ping
Recommends: gir1.2-ayatanaappindicator3-0.1, gir1.2-notify-0.7
Maintainer: Jonaz Thern <jonaz@thern.io>
Homepage: https://github.com/TheJonaz/wg-gtk-client
Description: Minimal GTK desktop client for WireGuard
 Start, stop and monitor a WireGuard tunnel from a small GTK window with
 live graphs, a kill switch, a connection watchdog, reconnect-on-network-change
 and dual-stack public-IP reporting. Privileged actions go through pkexec; no
 daemon and no stored credentials.
